          <node refid="T5" role="Co-theme"/>
        </relation>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">6</infon>
        <offset>803</offset>
        <text>This behaviour was associated to differential photosynthetic performances.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">7</infon>
        <offset>878</offset>
        <text>In the tropical strains, the rapid photosystem II inactivation and the decrease of the antioxydant beta-carotene relative to chl a suggested a strong induction of oxidative stress.
</text>
        <annotation id="T7">
          <infon key="brat-id">T7</infon>
          <infon key="type">Decrease</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="8" offset="949"/>
          <text>decrease</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T8">
          <infon key="brat-id">T8</infon>
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="29" offset="961"/>
          <text>the antioxydant beta-carotene</text>
        </annotation>
        <relation id="E4">
          <infon key="brat-id">E4</infon>
          <infon key="type">Decrease</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">event</infon>
          <node refid="T7" role="Decrease"/>
          <node refid="T8" role="Theme"/>
        </relation>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">8</infon>
        <offset>1059</offset>
        <text>These different responses were related to the thermal preferenda of the strains.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">9</infon>
        <offset>1140</offset>
        <text>The northern strains could grow at 10 degreesC while the other strains preferred higher temperatures.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">10</infon>
        <offset>1242</offset>
        <text>In addition, we pointed out a correspondence between strain isolation temperature and phylogeny.
</text>
        <annotation id="T9">
          <infon key="brat-id">T9</infon>
          <infon key="type">Correlate</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="22" offset="1272"/>
          <text>correspondence between</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T10">
          <infon key="brat-id">T10</infon>
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="28" offset="1295"/>
          <text>strain isolation temperature</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T12">
          <infon key="brat-id">T12</infon>
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="9" offset="1328"/>
          <text>phylogeny</text>
        </annotation>
        <relation id="E5">
          <infon key="brat-id">E5</infon>
          <infon key="type">Correlate</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">event</infon>
          <node refid="T9" role="Correlate"/>
          <node refid="T10" role="Theme"/>
          <node refid="T12" role="Co-theme"/>
        </relation>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">11</infon>
        <offset>1339</offset>
        <text>In particular, clades I and IV laboratory strains were all collected in the coldest waters of the distribution area of marine Synechococus.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">12</infon>
        <offset>1479</offset>
        <text>We, however, show that clade I Synechococcus exhibit different levels of adaptation, which apparently reflect their location on the latitudinal temperature gradient.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">13</infon>
        <offset>1645</offset>
        <text>This study reveals the existence of lineages of marine Synechococcus physiologically specialised in different thermal niches, therefore suggesting the existence of temperature ecotypes within the marine Synechococcus radiation.
</text>
      </sentence>
